:::I am happy to list these sources in a more presentable fashion:
:::*[http://books.google.com/books?id=xR7MdpuSlAEC ''All Music Guide: The Definitive Guide to Popular Music''] - Edited by [[allmusic]] critics [[Vladimir Bogdanov (editor)|Vladimir Bogdanov]], Chris Woodstra and [[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] and published by [[Hal Leonard Corporation]] in 2001. Publisher is recognized as a reliable source under [[Wikipedia:Verifiability#Reliable_sources|WP:Reliable Sources]]. Scaruffi's review of ''Country Boy Country Dog'' by "Blue" Gene Tyranny", as it was originally published in ''[[i/e magazine]]'', is presented in its entirety on page 1126.
:::*[http://books.google.com/books?id=beGNAQAAQBAJ ''Encyclopedia of American Gospel Music''] - Written by American folklorist, historian, record producer [[W.K. McNeil]] and published through [[Routledge]], Oct 18, 2013. Publisher is recognized as a reliable source under [[Wikipedia:Verifiability#Reliable_sources|WP:Reliable Sources]]. Author cites Scaruffi's book ''The History of Rock Music'' on page 253 as a reference and for further reading.
:::*[http://books.google.com/books?id=8xJr-StwLZsC ''Music of the World War II Era''] - Written by professors William H. Young and Nancy K. Young and published through [[Greenwood Publishing Group]], 2008. Publisher is recognized as a reliable source under [[Wikipedia:Verifiability#Reliable_sources|WP:Reliable Sources]]. On page 235, the authors assert that "Piero Scaruffi provides a good overview of rhythm n' blues in ''A Brief History of Rhythm and Blues''" before citing his webpage.
:::*[http://books.google.com/books?id=Q8qoUd6s4H4C&pg=PA237&dq=piero+scaruffi+allmusic&hl=en&sa=X&ei=yHheU7P6IqKTyQHY6oDQCA&ved=0CC0Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=piero%20scaruffi%20allmusic&f=false ''Sympathy for the Devil: Art and Rock and Roll Since 1967''] Written by Dominic Molon, published by [[Yale University Press]] in 2007. Cites "A Brief Summary of Japanese Rock Music" on page 133.
:::*[http://books.google.com/books?id=Z-BhAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA133&dq=scaruffi&hl=en&sa=X&ei=63peU6zHH6GSyQHZ74CQCw&ved=0CEcQ6AEwBTgU#v=onepage&q=scaruffi&f=false ''Women Drummers: A History from Rock and Jazz to Blues and Country'']. Written by writer and musician Angela Smith, published by [[Scarecrow Press]] on April 10, 2014. Quotes Mr. Scaruffi's book ''A History of Rock and Dance Music'' on pg. 133 and credits him with "providing historical context" in Acknowledgments on pg. xii.
:::*There was also some confusion as to whether or not ''[[Option (music magazine)|Option]]'', ''Sound Choice'', ''CD Review'', ''[[i/e]]'', ''[[Rockerilla]]'', ''[[Blow Up (magazine)|Blow Up]]'' and ''New Sounds'' meet [[Wikipedia:Verifiability#Reliable_sources|WP:Reliable Sources]].
